defaultThe Optical Confederation represents the 12,000 optometrists, the 6,000 dispensing opticians and 7,000 optical businesses in the UK who provide high quality and accessible eye care ser
defaultvices to the whole 
defaultpopulation. 
defaultThe Confederation is a coalition of the five optical representative bodies: the Association of British Dispensing Opticians (ABDO); the Association of Contact Lens Manufacturers (ACLM); the Association of Optometrists (AOP); the Federation of M
defaultanufacturing Opticians (FMO) and the Federation of Ophthalmic and Dispensing Opticians (FODO).
default As a Confederation, we work with others to improve eye health for the public good. 
