default&#xa0;default3.default defaultITdefault default&#xa0;
default3.1 
defaultIn line with the NHS’s vision for referrals to be completely paperless
default by 2018, the
default interconnectivity of community optical, GP, Choose and Book and hospital eye service IT systems should be 
defaultmade a
default priority
default by government
default as it will enable rapid exchange of clinical, referral, financial and audit data. The Scottish Government 
defaultis already making good progress towards this goal and, as a Confederation, we warmly welcomed NHS England’s announcement in June 2012 that they were in the early stages of developing a national specification for primary ophthalmic services (POS) claims and
default payments, an important first step towards greater connectivity in England and collecting outcomes data. We look forward to working with all relevant stakeholders to achieve integrated IT systems, as mentioned above, as their absence is a major obstacle to
default integrated eye care.
